  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The roof lights within the property are unacceptable in terms of their design and elevated position. They do not respect the architectural or historic integrity of the existing grade II listed building and are harmful to the character and appearance of the New River Conservation Area, and the setting of adjoining grade II listed buildings. The roof lights are contrary to policies D1 (Overall Design), D3 (Site Planning), D4 (Designing in Context) and D11 (Alterations and Extensions) of the UDP (2002), the Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002) the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006) and PPG15 'Planning and the Historic Environment'."
